33:25.406 --> 33:26.431
Yeah, this is Finn.

33:26.432 --> 33:29.435
He's in the Army, so we really
haven't been talking much lately.

33:29.436 --> 33:33.384
I had a girlfriend back home
when I first started NYADA.

33:33.385 --> 33:36.363
Yeah, we lasted six weeks.

33:36.364 --> 33:37.812
No, that's not gonna happen to us.

33:37.813 --> 33:39.391
I'm not gonna turn my back on him.

33:39.392 --> 33:40.522
Oh, nobody said you should.

33:40.523 --> 33:46.371
Anyway, I came to tell you
that you killed it in Tibideaux's class.

33:46.372 --> 33:47.384
Nice job.

33:47.385 --> 33:48.384
Thank you.

33:48.385 --> 33:51.435
You know, it's just, other than
when I was singing that song,

33:51.436 --> 33:57.421
I've just really never felt as
amazingly wrong as I do here.

33:57.422 --> 34:00.392
Just all alone.

34:00.393 --> 34:03.398
Kind of feel like I'm just
gonna throw up all the time.

34:04.439 --> 34:07.798
Well, it's just because you're
becoming a different person.

34:07.799 --> 34:09.388
That's why you came to New York.

34:09.389 --> 34:13.405
To be that new and improved girl.

34:13.406 --> 34:15.376
Here, let me see your phone.

34:15.377 --> 34:16.527
We're gonna take a picture.

34:20.393 --> 34:22.376
Let me see.

34:22.377 --> 34:23.447
You look good.

34:23.447 --> 34:26.376
Don't fight the new you.

34:26.377 --> 34:29.376
Because from what I've seen,

34:29.377 --> 34:32.388
she is gonna kick some serious tail.

34:32.389 --> 34:36.371
And start adding
new memories to the old ones.

34:38.447 --> 34:40.398
Walk you to class?

34:43.435 --> 34:44.547
What's the problem, people?

34:44.549 --> 34:46.388
You've been here a week.

34:46.389 --> 34:47.726
You should be dancing at, like,

34:47.728 --> 34:50.391
<i>Black Swan </i> levels
of psychosis right now.

34:50.393 --> 34:52.400
You, Miss Schwimmer.

34:52.402 --> 34:54.406
Show me your piqué.

34:56.406 --> 34:58.392
Okay, give me another one.

34:58.393 --> 35:00.393
Center yourself this time.

35:03.443 --> 35:05.455
Better, slightly.

35:05.456 --> 35:08.371
You gonna roll your eyes at me now?

35:08.372 --> 35:10.363
No.

35:10.364 --> 35:14.392
And I'm gonna keep getting better
till I'm the best you've ever seen.

35:14.393 --> 35:16.371
Oh, you're mouthy.

35:16.372 --> 35:17.443
And you got guts.

35:17.444 --> 35:19.417
Good, I like it.

35:19.418 --> 35:22.413
I like that spirit in my students.

35:22.414 --> 35:24.442
'Cause it'll make it more fun for me

35:24.443 --> 35:28.393
when I'm making your every
waking moment a hell on earth.

35:32.945 --> 35:34.020
So boring.

35:39.567 --> 35:42.395
All right.

35:42.399 --> 35:43.898
As soon as you find a place to live,

35:43.928 --> 35:45.809
I'll ship you the rest of your stuff.

35:45.810 --> 35:47.778
And you'll get enough cash
from selling your car

35:47.804 --> 35:50.156
to get you through at least
two weeks in a motel.

35:50.157 --> 35:53.156
And the emergency credit
card, which is only for what?

35:53.157 --> 35:55.056
Emergencies.
Dad, this is silly.

35:55.057 --> 35:57.143
I don't have to be in New York
to reapply for NYADA.

35:57.144 --> 35:59.024
So I can find a job
that pays me the same amount

35:59.025 --> 36:01.148
as Lima Bean, but pay
ten times more in rent?

36:01.149 --> 36:03.156
Yeah, because it's an adventure.

36:03.157 --> 36:06.202
Look, all great artists need a
little struggle in their lives.

36:06.203 --> 36:08.166
Didn't you tell me that Julia Roberts

36:08.167 --> 36:10.181
sold shoes in New York
before she made it?

36:10.182 --> 36:13.182
Good enough for Pretty Woman,
good enough for Kurt Hummel.

36:16.149 --> 36:17.156
Scared?

36:17.157 --> 36:18.210
Terrified.

36:18.211 --> 36:21.181
New York is gonna be a
breeze compared to Lima.

36:21.182 --> 36:25.148
Think about all the crap you've been
putting up with the last couple years.

36:25.149 --> 36:27.424
You know the difference between
this place and New York?

36:27.425 --> 36:29.148
Decent bagels?

36:29.149 --> 36:31.145
New York is filled
with people like you.

36:31.146 --> 36:34.185
People who aren't
afraid to be different.

36:34.186 --> 36:37.178
You're gonna feel at home there.

36:39.178 --> 36:40.251
If you're not scared,

36:40.252 --> 36:42.518
just means you're not sticking
out your neck far enough.

36:42.519 --> 36:44.168
You truly are
the world's greatest dad.

36:44.169 --> 36:47.199
I know. It's written on the coffee
mug you got me for Father's Day.

36:47.200 --> 36:49.131
Now, get out of here.

36:49.132 --> 36:50.411
You're gonna miss your flight.

36:58.199 --> 37:00.223
I'm gonna miss you, Dad.

37:00.224 --> 37:03.145
You can always come back.

37:08.216 --> 37:10.207
But you won't.

37:13.211 --> 37:16.127
I love you.

37:16.128 --> 37:18.190
I love you, too, Kurt.

37:37.182 --> 37:41.224
Hey, Marley, just wanted to apologize
for all of us and beg you not to quit.

37:41.225 --> 37:43.765
Look, I get you.

37:43.766 --> 37:46.199
Like, for instance, I know that
that sweater is from Walmart

37:46.200 --> 37:47.970
and your mom sewed the
J.Crew label into it.

37:47.971 --> 37:49.140
How do you know that?

37:49.141 --> 37:51.136
Because my mom used to do
the same thing for me.

37:51.137 --> 37:54.203
The best thing about Glee Club
is it's not about labels.

37:54.204 --> 37:56.203
If you can sing, if you can dance,

37:56.204 --> 37:58.223
you belong.

37:58.224 --> 37:59.224
And, dude, you can sing.

37:59.225 --> 38:02.127
I don't know.
You say that,

38:02.128 --> 38:04.185
but the way you were
making fun of my mom,

38:04.186 --> 38:06.185
something doesn't feel right.

38:06.186 --> 38:08.210
We came to apologize.

38:08.211 --> 38:11.134
I think being popular
felt a little too good,

38:11.135 --> 38:12.172
and we forgot ourselves.

38:12.173 --> 38:14.034
Well, I didn't.
I was always popular,

38:14.035 --> 38:16.147
but I do forget to wear
underwear sometimes, though.

38:16.148 --> 38:19.168
The best part about Glee Club is
that everyone gets to be a star.

38:19.169 --> 38:20.930
Which is why we're all
hoping that you could

38:20.931 --> 38:22.564
come to rehearsal
with us this afternoon,

38:22.565 --> 38:25.172
and maybe sing lead vocal on one
of the songs we're working on.

38:25.173 --> 38:26.495
And if words don't convince you,

38:26.496 --> 38:30.128
let the majesty and mystery of
Unique's <i>fabulousness </i> be enough!

38:31.136 --> 38:32.173
I mean it.

38:32.174 --> 38:33.324
Glee Club's a special place.

38:33.325 --> 38:36.006
I mean, where else
could I dress like this,

38:35.207 --> 38:37.344
and be welcomed with open arms?

38:38.145 --> 38:39.222
Okay, one last thing.

38:39.223 --> 38:41.703
I don't think I'm comfortable
sitting with that cheerleader

38:41.704 --> 38:44.139
and those guys at lunch.

38:44.140 --> 38:45.151
That won't be a problem.

38:45.152 --> 38:47.931
We could handle Gimpy and the
Tarantula Head and Richie Poor,

38:47.932 --> 38:50.426
because you guys were
national champs like us,

38:50.487 --> 38:53.189
but our invitation was not
extended to pre-op Precious

38:53.190 --> 38:55.182
based on the novel <i>Barf </i> by Sapphire

38:55.183 --> 38:58.148
and Mike and Molly's daughter
as part of our crew.

38:58.149 --> 39:01.127
Well, I guess we're not
in your crew anymore.

39:01.128 --> 39:03.199
You know, I was kind of hoping
you'd say that.

39:06.161 --> 39:08.216
And with that, order is restored.

39:11.186 --> 39:15.136
Well, looks like you guys have been
officially welcomed to the Glee Club.

39:15.137 --> 39:17.210
